## Bottom Line

The entire vector layer — LSH projection, hash key construction, bi-directional cursor expansion, exact distance reranking — is pure computation that belongs in C. WaveDB's C library already provides the sorted cursor primitive that SK-LSH was designed for. The `VectorLayer` becomes a C library (`libvector_layer.a` / `libvector_layer.so`) that links against `libwavedb`, with a header that any C project can include.

The only question is the exact signature of WaveDB's C cursor API — but the stream scan benchmark confirms the capability exists. You'd need to check the actual `wavedb.h` header (or the source in the `wavedb` package) for the precise function names and signatures, then code against those.

